results.name: a(n) = smallest number m such that m*tau(m)/sigma(m) = n, or 0 if no such m exists.
mathematica: f[n_] := (n*DivisorSigma[0, n]/DivisorSigma[1, n]); a = Table[0, {50}]; Do[ b = f[n]; If[ IntegerQ[b] && b < 51 && a[[b]] == 0, a[[b]] = n], {n, 1, 10 ^7}]; a
xref: The zeros occur at the complement of A090240.
